ecca Bartke-Croughan, Robin Rombach, Michael Flashman, Tomas Matteson, Simon Mathis, Alexander W. R. Nelson, David Yuan, Annette Obika, Simon A. A. Kohl | published=2025-07-25 | primary_category=q-bio.BM | id=2507.19375]\n  3. Latent-Autoregressive GP-VAE Language Model\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.09535\n     [authors=Yves Ruffenach | published=2025-12-10 | primary_category=cs.LG | id=2512.09535]\n  4. Forward Attention in Sequence-to-sequence Acoustic Modelling for Speech Synthesis\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.06736\n     [authors=Jing-Xuan Zhang, Zhen-Hua Ling, Li-Rong Dai | published=2018-07-18 | primary_category=cs.CL | id=1807.06736]\n  5. Acoustic modeling for Overlapping Speech Recognition: JHU Chime-5 Challenge System\n     https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.11078\n     [authors=Vimal Manohar, Szu-Jui Chen, Zhiqi Wang, Yusuke Fujita, Shinji Watanabe, Sanjeev Khudanpur | published=2024-05-17 | primary_category=eess.AS | id=2405.11078]\n\n=== openalex (5 results) ===\n  1. Continuous Sign Language Recognition and Its Translation into Intonation-Colored Speech\n     https://openalex.org/W4384341105\n     [rank=1 | id=W4384341105]\n  2. Data Augmentation based Cross-Lingual Multi-Speaker TTS using DL with Sentiment Analysis\n     https://openalex.org/W4387869282\n     [rank=2 | id=W4387869282]\n  3. The NU Non-Parallel Voice Conversion System for the Voice Conversion Challenge 2018\n     https://openalex.org/W2810457573\n     [rank=3 | id=W2810457573]\n  4. PromptStyle: Controllable Style Transfer for Text-to-Speech with Natural Language Descriptions\n     https://openalex.org/W4379251367\n     [rank=4 | id=W4379251367]\n  5. M3-TTS: Multi-modal DiT Alignment &amp; Mel-latent for Zero-shot High-fidelity Speech Synthesis\n     https://openalex.org/W4417086913\n     [rank=5 | id=W4417086913]\n\n=== openreview (5 results) ===\n  1. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?id=qcPzwlOflS\n     [authors= | rank=1 | id=qcPzwlOflS]\n  2. \n     https://openreview.net/forum?